oose to be paid either weekly in advance, or every 4 weeks or 13 weeks. </p>\n\n<p>All benefits, pensions and allowances are paid <a href=\"/how-to-have-your-benefits-paid\" title=\"how to have your benefits paid\">into an account</a>, eg your bank account.</p>\n\n<h2>If your circumstances change</h2>\n\n<p>Tell the Carer&rsquo;s Allowance Unit if your circumstances change as this can affect how much you get. Examples of changes include income, employment, holidays or stays in hospital. </p>\n\n<p>You can do this online, by phone or by post.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Carer’s Allowance Unit</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dwp.gov.uk/carersallowance\" title=\"Carer's Allowance e-service\" rel=\"external\">Report changes online</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone</strong>: 0845 608 4321  <br />\n<strong>Textphone</strong>: 0845 604 5312<br />\nMonday to Thursday, 8:30am to 5pm<br />\nFriday, 8:30am to 4:30pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nCarer's Allowance Unit \n<br />Palatine House \n<br />Lancaster Road \n<br />Preston PR1 1HB\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>From April 2013 a limit will be put on the total amount of benefit that most people aged 16 to 64 can get. This is called a <a href=\"/benefit-cap\" title=\"benefit cap\">benefit cap</a>.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/carers-allowance/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"<h2>Conditions -  you must meet</h2>\n\n<p>You might get Carer&rsquo;s Allowance if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>are 16 or over</li>\n  <li>spend at least 35 hours a week caring for someone</li>\n  <li>have been in the UK or the Isle of Man for at least 26 weeks in the 12 months before you claim</li>\n  <li>are in the UK when you claim - there are some exceptions, eg members and family members of the Armed Forces</li>\n  <li>aren&rsquo;t subject to immigration control</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Conditions - the person you care for</h2>\n\n<p>The person you care for must get one of these benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Attendance Allowance</li>\n  <li>Disability Living Allowance - the middle or highest care rate</li>\n  <li>Constant Attendance Allowance at or above the normal maximum rate with an Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit</li>\n  <li>Constant Attendance Allowance at the basic (full day) rate with a War Disablement Pension</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Use the <a href=\"/benefits-adviser\" title=\"Benefits adviser\">benefits adviser</a> to check your eligibility.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Exceptions</h2>\n\n<p>You may not get Carer&rsquo;s Allowance if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re in full-time education, and studying for 21 hours a week or more (this includes supervised study and things like coursework and experiments, not just time spent with a tutor)</li>\n  <li>you earn more than £100 a week (after tax)</li>\n  <li>you get one of the benefits listed below</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you get any of the benefits listed below and they pay you £58.45 or more you may not get Carer&rsquo;s Allowance. Instead, Jobcentre plus will work out if these benefits can be increased or if you&rsquo;re entitled to other benefits.  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Bereavement Allowance</li>\n  <li>contribution-based Employment and Support Allowance</li>\n  <li>contribution-based Jobseeker’s Allowance </li>\n  <li>Incapacity Benefit</li>\n  <li>Industrial Death Benefit</li>\n  <li>Maternity Allowance</li>\n  <li>Severe Disablement Allowance</li>\n  <li>State Pension</li>\n  <li>training allowance</li>\n  <li>Unemployability Supplement – paid with Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit or War Pension</li>\n  <li>War Widow’s or Widower’s Pension</li>\n  <li>Widowed Mother’s Allowance</li>\n  <li>Widowed Parent’s Allowance</li>\n  <li>Widow’s Pension</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/carers-allowance/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":