 to know</h2>\n\n<p>If someone else looks after the same person, only one of you can get Carer&rsquo;s Allowance.</p>\n\n<p>If you were entitled to Carer&rsquo;s Allowance before claiming it, you can ask for it to be backdated for up to 3 months.</p>\n\n<h2>Appeal a decision</h2>\n\n<p>You can appeal a decision about your Carer&rsquo;s Allowance if you&rsquo;re unhappy with it. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@benefits/documents/digitalasset/dg_201702.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Leaflet GL24 - Appeal against a benefit decision' (PDF, 4915KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Leaflet GL24 - Appeal against a benefit decision’ (PDF, 4.9MB)</a></p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/carers-allowance/further-information","slug":"further-information","order":5,"title":"Further information","body":"<h2>Effect on other benefits</h2>\n\n<p>Call the helpline for advice on how Carer&rsquo;s Allowance affects other benefits. </p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Benefit Enquiry Helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0800 88 22 00<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0800 24 33 55<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8:30am to 6:30pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Your benefits</h2>\n\n<p>If you get Housing Benefit or Council Tax Benefit you&rsquo;ll get extra towards these (called a &lsquo;carer premium&rsquo;). </p>\n\n<p>If you get the following benefits you&rsquo;ll get extra Carer&rsquo;s Allowance, but these benefits are then reduced by that amount: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Income Support</li>\n  <li>income-based Jobseeker&rsquo;s Allowance</li>\n  <li>Pension Credit</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Underlying entitlement</h2>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t normally get 2 income-replacement benefits (eg Carer&rsquo;s Allowance and the State Pension) paid together. </p>\n\n<p>This is called the &lsquo;overlapping benefit rule&rsquo;. If you can&rsquo;t be paid Carer&rsquo;s Allowance because of this rule, you have &lsquo;underlying entitlement&rsquo; to Carer&rsquo;s Allowance instead.</p>\n\n<p>This might mean you could get:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the carer premiums in Jobseeker&rsquo;s Allowance and Income Support</li>\n  <li>the extra amount for carers in Pension Credit</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Your State Pension</h2>\n\n<p>Usually, for each week you get Carer&rsquo;s Allowance or the underlying entitlement you also get: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/boost-state-pension\" title=\"National Insurance Credits\">National Insurance credits</a>  </li>\n  <li>contributions to your <a href=\"/additional-state-pension\" title=\"Additional State Pension\">Additional State Pension</a> </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Credits help to fill in any gaps in your National Insurance record. This can mean that you’ll still get the full State Pension and other benefits. These credits generally stop: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>in the tax year you reach State Pension age</li>\n  <li>if you get the underlying entitlement and Widow&rsquo;s Benefit or Bereavement Benefit</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>The person you care for</h2>\n\n<p>Carer&rsquo;s Allowance can affect the person you care for, eg their: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>severe disability premiums</li>\n  <li>Pension Credit - severe disability element </li>\n</ul>\n\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Carers and disability benefits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits%2Fdisability.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes Disability Living Allowance, Carer's Allowance and Employment and Support Allowance","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=benefits%2Fdisability","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/benefits/disability"},"parent":{"title":"Benefits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes tax credits and eligibility","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=benefits","web_url":"https