 a person who can&rsquo;t manage their own affairs. For example, because they&rsquo;re disabled or mentally ill. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You’re not an appointee if you just help someone complete their claim form.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How to become a tax credit appointee</h2>\n\n<p>Complete the appointee section on the tax credit claim form. You must be over 18 and have a bank account. You don&rsquo;t have to be a relative. </p>\n\n<h3>Your responsibilities</h3>\n\n<p>You must: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>sign the tax credit claim form</li>\n  <li>renew the tax credits claim </li>\n  <li>report any changes which affect how much money the person gets</li>\n  <li>tell the Tax Credit Office if you&rsquo;re no longer the appointee</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Any tax credits the person gets are paid directly into your bank account. If you make a false or misleading application you may be charged a penalty. </p>\n\n<h2>Stop being an appointee</h2>\n\n<p>Write to the Tax Credit Office within 1 month of when you want to stop being the appointee. </p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nTax Credit Office\n<br />Preston\n<br />PR1 4AT\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/getting-help-with-your-tax-credits-claim/claim-on-behalf-of-your-child","slug":"claim-on-behalf-of-your-child","order":3,"title":"Claim on behalf of your child","body":"<h2>Your child is under 16</h2>\n\n<p>If your child has a baby, you can make the claim for both of them if they live with you. The money will be paid to you. </p>\n\n<h2>Your child is over 16</h2>\n\n<p>If your child is over 16 and has a baby, they can make the claim themselves. The money will be paid to them. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If the child and baby live with you - you may also be entitled to tax credits.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Tax credits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits%2Ftax-credits.json","web_url":null,"details":{