ase (&lsquo;discharge&rsquo;) the patient or recommend they are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>transferred to a local hospital</li>\n  <li>considered for treatment in the community</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The patient is sometimes allowed some time out of the hospital, to see if they&rsquo;re ready for life in the community.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The tribunal deals with cases in England and Wales. <a href=\"http://www.mhtscotland.gov.uk/mhts/Home/Welcome_to_the_Mental_Health_Tribunal\" title=\"Scotland\" rel=\"external\">Scotland</a> has its own tribunal.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Other applications</h2>\n\n<p>You can also apply to the tribunal if you disagree with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a community treatment order</li>\n  <li>the conditions placed on a discharge from the hospital</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When you can apply</h2>\n\n<p>You can apply at different times, depending on how the patient was detained.</p>\n\n<p>The rules are complicated, but generally the time-limits are:</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Type of detention</th>\n      <th>Period of detention</th>\n      <th>When you can appeal</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Admitted for assessment</td>\n      <td>Up to 28 days</td>\n      <td>Within first 14 days</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Admitted for treatment</td>\n      <td>Up to 6 months, but can be renewed</td>\n      <td>Once every 6 months</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Ordered by court</td>\n      <td>Up to 6 months, but can be renewed</td>\n      <td>After 6 months, then once every 6 months</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The tribunal will automatically look at the cases of patients that have not been reviewed for some time. These are called &lsquo;referrals&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<h2>Help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>Patients are entitled to <a href=\"/legal-aid\" title=\"legal aid\">legal aid</a> and can get free legal representation.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a relative of the patient, you can represent yourself or get legal help.</p>\n\n<p>You can find a mental health solicitor on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.lawsocietyapproved.com/mental_health.aspx\" title=\"Law Society website\">Law Society website.</a></p>\n\n<p>You can also get advice from:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.nhs.uk/carersdirect/carerslives/updates/pages/carersdirecthelpline.aspx\" title=\"Carers Direct\">Carers Direct</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.mind.org.uk/\" title=\"Mind\">Mind</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.rethink.org/\" title=\"Rethink\">Rethink</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/mental-health-tribunal/apply-to-tribunal","slug":"apply-to-tribunal","order":2,"title":"Apply to the tribunal","body":"<p>To apply to the tribunal in England and Wales, fill in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2732\" title=\"Application to First–tier Tribunal (Mental Health)\">Application to First–tier Tribunal (Mental Health).</a></p>\n\n<p>Send the form to:</p>\n\n<h2>England</h2>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nFirst-tier Tribunal (Mental Health)  \n<br />PO Box 8793  \n<br />5th Floor  \n<br />Leicester  \n<br />LE1 8BN\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Wales</h2>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nMental Health Tribunal for Wales  \n<br />Crown Buildings  \n<br />Cathays Park  \n<br />Cardiff  \n<br />CF10 3NQ\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Mental health tribunal enquiries</strong><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#109;&#104;&#114;&#116;&#101;&#110;&#113;&#117;&#105;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#109;&#104;&#114;&#116;&#101;&#110;&#113;&#117;&#105;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;