cision at the end of the hearing on whether the patient should be discharged.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The tribunal sometimes has to move the hearing to another date if it needs more information or reports.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Claiming expenses</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to claim expenses for going to the hearing. This includes money for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>travel costs</li>\n  <li>loss of earnings</li>\n  <li>food and drink, if you&rsquo;re away for more than 5 hours</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Read the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2739\" title=\"guidance on claiming expenses\">guidance on claiming expenses.</a></p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/mental-health-tribunal/if-you-lose-case","slug":"if-you-lose-case","order":4,"title":"If you lose the case","body":"<p>If you lose your case, you can ask the tribunal:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>to look at the decision again</li>\n  <li>for permission to appeal to a higher tribunal</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must appeal within 28 days of getting the written decision.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Ask the tribunal to look at the decision again</h2>\n\n<p>You can ask the tribunal to look at the decision again if there was a problem with the way the case was handled, eg:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you didn&rsquo;t get important documents about the case</li>\n  <li>you or your representative weren&rsquo;t at the hearing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If there was a problem, the tribunal may be able to restart the case.</p>\n\n<p>Fill in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2740\" title=\"application to set aside a decision\">application to set aside a decision,</a> and return it to the mental health tribunal.</p>\n\n<h2>Appeal to the upper tribunal</h2>\n\n<p>You can ask for permission to appeal to the upper tribunal if you think there was a legal mistake.</p>\n\n<p>To do this, fill in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2742\" title=\"application for permission to appeal\">application for permission to appeal,</a> and return it to the mental health tribunal.</p>\n\n<p>Another judge will look to see if there&rsquo;s a legal problem with your case. If there is, the case may have to be heard again.</p>\n\n<p>Find out more about appealing to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/guidance/courts-and-tribunals/tribunals/aa/index.htm\" title=\"Upper Tribunal (Administrative Appeals Chamber)\">Upper Tribunal (Administrative Appeals Chamber).</a></p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Lasting Power of Attorney, being in care and your financial affairs","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/births-deaths-marriages%2Flasting-power-attorney.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes dealing with benefits, taxes and leaving care","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=births-deaths-marriages%2Flasting-power-attorney","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/births-deaths-marriages/lasting-power-attorney"},"parent":{"title":"Births, deaths, marriages and care","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/births-deaths-marriages.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes civil partnerships, splitting up and Lasting Power of Attorney","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=births-deaths-marriages","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/births-deaths-marriages"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Courts, sentencing and tribunals","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Attending courts, paying fines, appealing a sentence and tribunals","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Fcourts-se